										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>
<div>
<p>Love when a synth sounds organic, the closer it gets to the characteristic of a voice, the better. But loving such sounds doesn&#8217;t mean you know how to make them; Yet.<br />In a sense, It&#8217;s a bit like when you find your most liked <span>Here is the original sound. Some information we can gather already: The synth is mono, with just a little bit of reverb. It’s apparently a saw wave, with a lot of filtering to give it that organic sound, and some notes seems to glide into each other, much like someone would do when singing.</span> </p>
</div>
</div>
<h3>Here&#8217;s how to awawa: <span>Megata,</span> the acid lead.</h3>
<div>
<p>Here is the original sound. Some information we can gather already: The synth is mono, with just a little bit of reverb. It&#8217;s apparently a saw wave, with a lot of filtering to give it that organic sound, and some notes seems to glide into each other, much like someone would do when singing.</p>
</p>
</div>
<div>
<p>    <iframe loading="lazy" width="100%" height="166" scrolling="no" frameborder="no" allow="autoplay" src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/1044336028%3Fsecret_token%3Ds-uAFJ7UvAkww&#038;color=%23171717&#038;auto_play=false&#038;hide_related=false&#038;show_comments=true&#038;show_user=true&#038;show_reposts=false&#038;show_teaser=true"></iframe></p>
<div style="font-size: 10px; color: #cccccc;line-break: anywhere;word-break: normal;overflow: hidden;white-space: nowrap;text-overflow: ellipsis; font-family: Interstate,Lucida Grande,Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Sans,Garuda,Verdana,Tahoma,sans-serif;font-weight: 100;"><a href="https://soundcloud.com/arkadatazk" title="ARKADATA" target="_blank" style="color: #cccccc; text-decoration: none;">ARKADATA</a> · <a href="https://soundcloud.com/arkadatazk/megata-kyojin-kuchiku-original/s-uAFJ7UvAkww" title="Megata Kyojin Kuchiku Original" target="_blank" style="color: #cccccc; text-decoration: none;">Megata Kyojin Kuchiku Original</a></div>
</div>
<div>
<p>Now that I have a basic idea of what the sound consists of in terms of sound design. Let&#8217;s check the melody to make a copy as close as possible to the original.</p>
<p>I&#8217;ll use a piano for that purpose.</p>
</div>
<div>
<p>    <iframe loading="lazy" width="100%" height="166" scrolling="no" frameborder="no" allow="autoplay" src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/1044336604%3Fsecret_token%3Ds-Et3RNPlOxzj&#038;color=%23171717&#038;auto_play=false&#038;hide_related=false&#038;show_comments=true&#038;show_user=true&#038;show_reposts=false&#038;show_teaser=true"></iframe></p>
<div style="font-size: 10px; color: #cccccc;line-break: anywhere;word-break: normal;overflow: hidden;white-space: nowrap;text-overflow: ellipsis; font-family: Interstate,Lucida Grande,Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Sans,Garuda,Verdana,Tahoma,sans-serif;font-weight: 100;"><a href="https://soundcloud.com/arkadatazk" title="ARKADATA" target="_blank" style="color: #cccccc; text-decoration: none;">ARKADATA</a> · <a href="https://soundcloud.com/arkadatazk/swn-megata-keikaku-pfver/s-Et3RNPlOxzj" title="SWN Megata Keikaku PFver" target="_blank" style="color: #cccccc; text-decoration: none;">SWN Megata PFver</a></div>
</div>
<div>
<p>Next, I&#8217;m gonna use one of my synths to get as close as possible to the original sound. Zebra from u-He has a lot of good filtering possibilities along with a good legato system. It should be able to do the job, though results may vary slightly from the original due to how differents synths can sound. </p>
<p>Anyway, the goal here isn&#8217;t to achieve a 100% copy. It&#8217;s to understand a craft; we are learning a recipe to make many variations of that kind of sound.</p>
</div>
<p><img src="https://i.imgur.com/WN9zUeL.png" alt=""></p>
<ul>
<li>
<h3>Filter KeyFollow</h3>
<div>
<p>Great way to add variation on our filter. Have its cutoff follow the current note.</p>
</div>
</li>
<li>
<h3>Filter KeyFollow</h3>
<div>
<p>Most important aspect of our filter. It needs to follow a medium-slow release.</p>
</div>
</li>
</ul>
<div>
<p>I ended up using a lot of different filters with different levels of resonance, with the cutoff that follows an envelope. Thanks to how Zebra handle things, the filter<strong> does not reset</strong> when playing legato. </p>
<p>A simple mono saw wave with a single voice does the job for the OSC. The LP Filters will do the rest.</p>
<p>What&#8217;s important is the glide and the filter&#8217;s motion. The thing with Megata&#8217;s synth is that it&#8217;s not always gliding/in legato. It&#8217;s humanized in a way, to give it some variation.</p>
</div>
<p><img src="https://i.imgur.com/dQXsYHA.png" alt=""></p>
<div>
<h3>Legato</h3>
<div>
<p>Notes that glides into each other, making that sweet organic effect.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<p>And there we have it. It&#8217;s not perfect but it&#8217;s quite close.</p>
</div>
<div>
<p>    <iframe loading="lazy" width="100%" height="166" scrolling="no" frameborder="no" allow="autoplay" src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/1044336316%3Fsecret_token%3Ds-9YmmvkhqHcU&#038;color=%23171717&#038;auto_play=false&#038;hide_related=false&#038;show_comments=true&#038;show_user=true&#038;show_reposts=false&#038;show_teaser=true"></iframe></p>
