										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>
<div>
<p><span>I’m fascinated by simple pieces that only use a string ensemble. No synths, no brass, no winds, no percussions.</span><br /><span>It’s a great exercise to reproduce such arrangements, especially when considering how much work can be put into production.</span></p>
</div>
</div>
<h3>Trying to reproduce a Japanese Orchestra with Cinematic Studio Strings.</h3>
<div>
<p>Here is the original soundtrack from Sawano Hiroyuki. It&#8217;s a 3min54 strings piece, with a classical feel.</p>
</div>
<div>
<p>    <iframe loading="lazy" width="100%" height="166" scrolling="no" frameborder="no" allow="autoplay" src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/1044417112%3Fsecret_token%3Ds-upxte4AHfT7&#038;color=%23171717&#038;auto_play=false&#038;hide_related=false&#038;show_comments=true&#038;show_user=true&#038;show_reposts=false&#038;show_teaser=true"></iframe></p>
<div style="font-size: 10px; color: #cccccc;line-break: anywhere;word-break: normal;overflow: hidden;white-space: nowrap;text-overflow: ellipsis; font-family: Interstate,Lucida Grande,Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Sans,Garuda,Verdana,Tahoma,sans-serif;font-weight: 100;"><a href="https://soundcloud.com/arkadatazk" title="ARKADATA" target="_blank" style="color: #cccccc; text-decoration: none;">ARKADATA</a> · <a href="https://soundcloud.com/arkadatazk/kanascene/s-upxte4AHfT7" title="kanascene" target="_blank" style="color: #cccccc; text-decoration: none;">kanascene</a></div>
</div>
<div>
<p>The first step to reproduce the piece was to get the main instruments and timing right. Starting with the violin as our leading voice.</p>
</div>
<div>
<p>    <iframe loading="lazy" width="100%" height="166" scrolling="no" frameborder="no" allow="autoplay" src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/1044422080%3Fsecret_token%3Ds-SSHyY4t9BkQ&#038;color=%23171717&#038;auto_play=false&#038;hide_related=false&#038;show_comments=true&#038;show_user=true&#038;show_reposts=false&#038;show_teaser=true"></iframe></p>
<div style="font-size: 10px; color: #cccccc;line-break: anywhere;word-break: normal;overflow: hidden;white-space: nowrap;text-overflow: ellipsis; font-family: Interstate,Lucida Grande,Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Sans,Garuda,Verdana,Tahoma,sans-serif;font-weight: 100;"><a href="https://soundcloud.com/arkadatazk" title="ARKADATA" target="_blank" style="color: #cccccc; text-decoration: none;">ARKADATA</a> · <a href="https://soundcloud.com/arkadatazk/kanascene-azkver2/s-SSHyY4t9BkQ" title="# Kanascene Azkver2" target="_blank" style="color: #cccccc; text-decoration: none;"># Kanascene Azkver2</a></div>
</div>
<div>
<p>I tried to get as close as possible with Cinematic Studio Strings, but the ensemble is a bit bigger than what was used on Aldnoah Zero&#8217;s soundtrack. Which used a Japanese studio orchestra (Muroya Strings), which is probably half the size of what I&#8217;m currently using.</p>
<p>A way I found to make up for that is to use solo strings in addition to the ensemble. It gives more definition to the sound.</p>
</div>
<div>
<p>    <iframe loading="lazy" width="100%" height="166" scrolling="no" frameborder="no" allow="autoplay" src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/1044422224%3Fsecret_token%3Ds-jDImmlje2OY&#038;color=%23171717&#038;auto_play=false&#038;hide_related=false&#038;show_comments=true&#038;show_user=true&#038;show_reposts=false&#038;show_teaser=true"></iframe></p>
<div style="font-size: 10px; color: #cccccc;line-break: anywhere;word-break: normal;overflow: hidden;white-space: nowrap;text-overflow: ellipsis; font-family: Interstate,Lucida Grande,Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Sans,Garuda,Verdana,Tahoma,sans-serif;font-weight: 100;"><a href="https://soundcloud.com/arkadatazk" title="ARKADATA" target="_blank" style="color: #cccccc; text-decoration: none;">ARKADATA</a> · <a href="https://soundcloud.com/arkadatazk/kanascene-azkver10/s-jDImmlje2OY" title="# Kanascene Azkver10" target="_blank" style="color: #cccccc; text-decoration: none;"># Kanascene Azkver10</a></div>
</div>
<div>
<p>It&#8217;s getting there but it still feels a bit stiff.</p>
<p>Some more work on the Cello to get all the notes and timing right. </p>
<p>I used a convolution reverb alongside an algorithmic one to get the sound I wanted. Which consists of an MCO5 IR (Studio Room) with differents mics placements and some FabFilter Pro-R.</p>
</div>
<h1>
<h3>Here&#8217;s the final result:</h3>
</h1>
<div>
<p>    <iframe loading="lazy" width="100%" height="166" scrolling="no" frameborder="no" allow="autoplay" src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/1044416836%3Fsecret_token%3Ds-XSlt0Hcu8nq&#038;color=%23171717&#038;auto_play=false&#038;hide_related=false&#038;show_comments=true&#038;show_user=true&#038;show_reposts=false&#038;show_teaser=true"></iframe></p>
<div style="font-size: 10px; color: #cccccc;line-break: anywhere;word-break: normal;overflow: hidden;white-space: nowrap;text-overflow: ellipsis; font-family: Interstate,Lucida Grande,Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Sans,Garuda,Verdana,Tahoma,sans-serif;font-weight: 100;"><a href="https://soundcloud.com/arkadatazk" title="ARKADATA" target="_blank" style="color: #cccccc; text-decoration: none;">ARKADATA</a> · <a href="https://soundcloud.com/arkadatazk/kanascene-azkver/s-XSlt0Hcu8nq" title="# Kanascene &lt;azk.ver&gt;" target="_blank" style="color: #cccccc; text-decoration: none;"># Kanascene &lt;azk.ver&gt;</a></div>
</div>
<div>
<p>The colors are quite different from the original, but I feel like the production value is quite there. <strong>It sounds.</strong> <br />Slightly more powerful, less intimate, probably due to the libraries being quite bigger in size than a traditional Japanese orchestra.</p>
</div>
